  • Method Details

    • setImpact

      public boolean setImpact​(java.awt.geom.Point2D point, int dir)
      setImpact method is for detecting if an impact has occured. If a brick is broken, return false, meaning no impact made. If a brick is not broken, run impact method and return if the brick is broken or not.
      Parameters:
      point - point of impact.
      dir - direction of impact.
      Returns:
      returns boolean value to check if brick is broken or not.
